==Demographics==

Haigler Creek is home to very few resident individuals or families with a population of just 39 as of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]. Many of the homes in the area are cabins or summer getaways for [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]] and [[Tucson, Arizona|Tucson]] locals, due to the cooler temperatures. The [[ZIP Code|ZIP code]] for Haigler creek is 85541 and the area code is 928.

In Haigler Creek the population is quite spread out with only 24.2 people per square mile. The median age is 65.3 years and the median household income is $13,583. There are 39 households in the area and 85 housing units which 46% are occupied. The median price of an owner occupied housing unit is $343,300. 33% of the people are married.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Census profile: Haigler Creek, AZ |url=http://censusreporter.org/profiles/16000US0430840-haigler-creek-az/ |access-date=June 21, 2022 |website=Census Reporter |language=en}}</ref>  
